g.text: Door: The doors seem to be on rails, but they've gotten jammed. You grab a side and put some strength into prying it open. With the help of your partner the two metal panels slide open with a *creak*.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes. Time to investigate these passages. Let's move quietly and not make more sound."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Officer? Are you okay in there?"
Empathy: He's quite proud of himself.
Kim Kitsuragi: "What do you mean 'who's there'? It's me, Kim. Stop playing around and help me get this door open."
Door: Two rusty metal plates that slide apart form a crude door. It's been here under the boardwalk for a while.
Savoir Faire: Not *running* is a great way to do that.
Kim Kitsuragi: "After you *climbed* up to the roof, you mean? There's a maintenance entrance under the boardwalk. It's next to a drain pipe, possibly a storm drain -- it was easy to miss before."
You: "Could have saved me the effort."
You: "How did you even get there?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, we have an exit. So, let's get going. Time to investigate these passages..." He peers into the darkness.
Door: It's *much* easier from this side -- the panels on the rails slide once you dust the sand off. With the help of your partner from the other side the doors open with a *creak*.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, yes, it's *cool* to risk your life climbing rickety ladders. Anyway, let's investigate these passages..."
Esprit de Corps: You really ought to open this door. It's dangerous to go ahead alone.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Huh, I hope no one *dangerous* heard that."
You: "At least now we know a quick way in and out."
Kim Kitsuragi: He shrugs. "At least now we have an exit. So, let's get going. It's time to investigate these passages..."
